<section>
   <h2>Purpose</h2>
   <p>Checkboxes and radio buttons with large touch targets to support behavioural patterns of interacting with the form element, and not the label.</p>
</section>
<section>
   <h2>Usage</h2>
   <div class="row wb-eqht mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-xl">
      <div class="col-md-6">
         <h3 class="mrgn-tp-0 text-success h4">Use when <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle"></span></h3>
         <ul>
            <li>Streamline complex navigation through multiple option.</li>
            <li>Use for interactive questions and checkboxes for services and wizards</li>
         </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 brdr-lft">
         <h3 class="mrgn-tp-0 text-danger h4">Do not use when <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove-circle"></span></h3>
         <ul>
            <li>Avoid using checkboxes or radio buttons if the options are not easily comparable. Consider navigation patterns such as a topic page</li>
            <li>If supporting navigation, for a small number of options, consider using expand/collapse or tabs</li>
         </ul>
      </div>
   </div>
</section>
<section>
   <h2>Working examples</h2>
   <h3>Checkboxes</h3>
   <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
         <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-body">
               <h5 class="mrgn-tp-0">Appearance</h5>
               <h6>Large checkboxes</h6>
               <ul class="list-unstyled gc-form">
                  <li class="checkbox">
                     <input type="checkbox" id="checkbox_1">
                     <label for="checkbox_1">Option 1</label>
                  </li>
                  <li class="checkbox">
                     <input type="checkbox" id="checkbox_2">
                     <label for="checkbox_2">Option 2</label>
                  </li>
                  <li class="checkbox">
                     <input type="checkbox" id="checkbox_3">
                     <label for="checkbox_3">Option 3</label>
                  </li>
                  <li class="checkbox">
                     <input type="checkbox" id="checkbox_4">
                     <label for="checkbox_4">Option 4</label>
                  </li>
               </ul>
               <hr>
               <h6>Small checkboxes</h6>
               <ul class="list-unstyled gc-form">
                  <li class="checkbox checkbox-small">
                     <input type="checkbox" id="confirmation-checkbox">
                     <label for="confirmation-checkbox">Single option</label>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
         <h5 class="mrgn-tp-0 text-success"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle"></span> Correct use</h5>
         <p>Compliance point(s):</p>
         <ul>
            <li>Use large checkboxes when one or more selections can be made to answer a question. It can also be used for a checklist, with short labels that do not break across lines.</li>
            <li>Use small checkboxes when making a checklist with items that would break across multiple lines or when there is a single item that can be checked.</li>
         </ul>
         <h5 class="mrgn-tp-0 text-danger"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove-circle"></span> Incorrect use</h5>
         <p>Compliance point(s):</p>
         <ul>
            <li>Do not use if there is a need for users to enter a detailed answer</li>
            <li>Do not use the small checkbox pattern in wizards or questions in forms</li>
         </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
         <h5 class="mrgn-tp-0">Code</h5>
